main event: A bright white object, approximately the size of a grapefruit, was observed in the sky over San Antonio, Texas on March 22-23, 1959.
interesting points: The object was observed at an altitude of approximately 1,000 feet, traveling southeast.
The object stopped and continued moving again, giving it a 'rocking effect'.
The observer described the object as having a 'tail' and there was a sound, but they could not determine if it came from the object.
The object was tracked by ground visual observation, without the use of any optical aids.
An investigation by Dr. Paul L. Seebass, Director of the Trinity University Geophysical Research Program, concluded that the object was likely an unusual type of weather phenomenon.
sighted object: A bright white object, approximately the size of a grapefruit
photographs: No photographs present in the report
